 son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705188,"age":3,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert de Mauduit III was born in 1221, in Great Somerford, Wiltshire, England, his father, Robert de Mauduit II, was 47 and his mother, Beatrice de Murdac, was 28. He had at least 2 sons. He died after 1251."},"et":{"1221–after 1251":"1221–pärast 1251","1221–1251":"1221–1251","1250–1302":"1250–1302","1255–1288":"1255–1288","1175–1245":"1175–1245","1194–1221":"1194–1221","1302":"1302","1224":"1224","1245":"1245","1288":"1288","1255":"1255","1221":"1221","1220":"1220","after 1251":"pärast 1251","1175":"1175","1251":"1251","1250":"1250","1194":"1194","England":"England","Great Somerford, Wiltshire, England":"Great Somerford, Wiltshire, England","Somerford, Wiltshire, England, Great Britain":"Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1221–after 1251":"1221–1251 jälkeen","1221–1251":"1221–1251","1250–1302":"1250–1302","1255–1288":"1255–1288","1175–1245":"1175–1245","1194–1221":"1194–1221","1302":"1302","1224":"1224","1245":"1245","1288":"1288","1255":"1255","1221":"1221","1220":"1220","after 1251":"1251 jälkeen","1175":"1175","1251":"1251","1250":"1250","1194":"1194","England":"England","Great Somerford, Wiltshire, England":"Great Somerford, Wiltshire, England","Somerford, Wiltshire, England, Great Britain":"Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1221–after 1251":"1221–après 1251","1221–1251":"1221–1251","1250–1302":"1250–1302","1255–1288":"1255–1288","1175–1